                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.1100 K77/95.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Nicaragua</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Presidential Mansion</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have the honor to apprize you of enthusiastic ovation for Secretary Knox and
                    family. Nicaragua considers herself honored by the visit of such illustrious and
                    welcome guests, and I take pleasure in thanking Your Excellency for it. I send
                    you my best wishes for your personal happiness and for the prosperity of the
                    American people over whom Your Excellency so worthily presides.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">President Díaz</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
